Exception Handling:
----------------------
An Exception is unexpected event that occurs during execution of program dusruption normal flow of instruction.
When a program encounters an error, it creates an object(which line number, which class , full trace details) and handover it to JVM and JVM prints this object to the console.

EX:
public class ArithmeticOperators {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a = 11;
        int b = 0;
        System.out.println("Division - "+ (a / b)); // Exception occurs here.
        //Control wont come down.
        System.out.println("Addition - "+ (a + b));
        System.out.println("Susbtraction - "+ (a - b));

    }
}
EX: trace:
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.ArithmeticException: / by zero
	at org.example.operators.ArithmeticOperators.main(ArithmeticOperators.java:9)

Exception often happens bcz of below reasons:
---------------------------------------------
User Input: A user enters ABC instead of number.
Hardware issue: Disk is full. When a program tries to create a file and if the disk is full, the file cant be created and the program fails.
Physical Limmit:  We have 4 items and if we try to access 8th item the we get exception and progrm halts. 


classifications:
-----------------
Fixable and Fatal
  Fixable errors are the ones that a programmer can handle and recover it from exception. ArithmeticExeption, NullpointerExeption
  Fatal errors are the ones that a programmer can t handle or cant be recovered.
  OutofMemory, stackoverflow 

